│ The `Scatterer` class is designed to handle scattered vectors or vector pointers, and   │
│ it relies on the `VectorSplit` structure to manage the splitting of vectors. The        │
│ `gather` function also expects a `VectorSplit` object to reassemble the scattered       │
│ components.                                                                             │
│                                                                                         │
│ The issue arises because the `llvm.uadd.with.overflow` intrinsic returns a mixed-type   │
│ structure (vector and scalar), which does not fit the `VectorSplit` model. To fix this, │
│ we need to handle mixed-type structures explicitly in the `visitExtractValueInst`       │
│ function without relying on `VectorSplit`.                                              │
│                                                                                         │
│ I will now refine the patch to address this issue.                                      │
